gurmukhi: ਜਿਤੇ ਜੁੱਝ ਰੁੱਝੇ || ਤਿਤੇ ਅੰਤ ਜੁੱਝੇ ||
transliteration: Jite Sujjh Rujjhe|| Tite Ant Jujjhe||
translation: Those who were active in the battlefield, they were all decimated.

transliteration: Jine Sastra Dhaale|| Tite Maar Daale||23||61||
translation: Those who caught hold of weapons, they were all killed.23.61.

gurmukhi: ਤਬੈ ਮਾਤ ਕਾਲੀ || ਤਪੀ ਤੇਜ ਜੁਵਾਲੀ ||
transliteration: Tabai Maat Kaaloo|| Tapoo Tej Juvaaloo||
translation: Then the mother Kali flared up like the flaming fire.

transliteration: Jisai Ghaav Ddaryo|| Su Suragadg Sidhdaryo||24||62||
translation: To whomsoever she struck, he departed for heaven.24.62.

gurmukhi: ਘਰੀ ਅੱਧ ਮੱਧੰ || ਹਨਯੋ ਸੈਨ ਸੁੱਧੰ ||
transliteration: Gdaroo Addh Maddhan|| Hanyo Sain Suddhan||
translation: The whole army was destroyed within a very short time.
Dhumar Nain was killed and the gods heard about it in heaven.25.63.

gurmukhi: ਭਜੀ ਬਿਰੂਥਨ ਦਾਨਵੀ ਗੲੀ ਭੂਪ ਕੇ ਪਾਸ ||
transliteration: Bhajoo Biroothan Daanavoo Gado Bhoop Ke Paas||
translation: The demon forces ran towards their king.

gurmukhi: ਧੂਮ੍ਰਨੈਣ ਕਾਲੀ ਹਨਯੋ ਭੱਜਯੋ ਸੈਨ ਨਿਰਾਸ ||੨੬||੬੪||
transliteration: Dhoomranain Kaaloo Hanyo Bhajjyo Sain Niraas||26||64||
translation: Intimating him that Kali had killed Dhumar Nain and the forces had fled in disappointment.26.64.

gurmukhi: ੲਿਤਿ ਸ੍ਰੀ ਬਚਿਤ੍ਰ ਨਾਟਕੇ ਚੰਡੀ ਚਰਿਤ੍ਰੇ ਧੂਮ੍ਰਨੈਣ ਬਧਹ ਦੁਤੀਅਾ ਧਿਅਾੲਿ ਸੰਪੂਰਣ ਸਸਤੁ ਸੁਭ ਮਸਤੁ ||੨|| ਅਫਜੂ ||
transliteration: It(i) Sroo Bachitra Natake Channdoo Charitre Dhoomranain Badhah Doutooaa Dhiaae Sanpooran Mast(u) Soubh Mast(u)||2|| Afjoo||
translation: Here ends the Second Chapter entitled ‘Killing of Dhumar Nain’, which forms part of Chandi Charitra of BACHITTAR NATAK.2.
Now the battle with Chand and Mund is described:

gurmukhi: ੲਿਹ ਬਿਧ ਦੈਤ ਸੰਘਾਰ ਕਰ ਧਵਲਾ ਚਲੀ ਅਵਾਸ ||
transliteration: Ih Bidh Dait Sanhaar Kar Dhavlaa Chaloo Avaas||
translation: In this way, killing the demons, the goddess Durga went to her abode.
